title: Grateful Dead Live at Olympia Theater on 1972-05-03
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Mr. Charlie, Sugaree, Black Throated Wind, Chinatown Shuffle, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Beat It On Down The Line, He's Gone, Next Time You See Me, Playin' In The Band, Tennessee Jed, Good Lovin', Sing Me Back Home, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, Ramble On Rose, It Hurts Me Too, Truckin'-> Space-> The Other One-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me And Bobby McGee-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat, Jack Straw, Sugar Magnolia, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

5/3/72 was one of the "Honeymoon" tapes that were taken from David Gans'house while he was away on his honeymoon.

reviews.review_text: Perfection Is it the quality of the playing?  The quality of the recording?  Or both?  Both!!  Nice job!  Honored to be the first reviewer of this recent upload.

Great Show, but needs pitch correction on E72' cuts.  The cuts from E72' that appear, Ten Jed, China Cat, He's Gone, are flat a half a semitone. It should also be noted that the vocals on these songs are studio overdubs. E72' is a hybrid live-studio album. Is there a copy of entire live performance or were these put in to cover splices in the master?
